Algorithm::A step-by-step procedure for solving a problem or performing a task.
Variable::A named storage location in memory that holds data (e.g., numbers, text).
Loop::A programming structure that repeats a set of instructions until a condition is met (e.g., for loop, while loop).
Function::A reusable block of code that performs a specific task.
Binary::A base-2 number system (using 0s and 1s) that computers use to process data.
Compiler::A program that translates high-level code (like Python or Java) into machine code.
Debugging::The process of finding and fixing errors (bugs) in code.
Array::A data structure that stores a collection of elements in a specific order.
Boolean::A data type with two values: True or False.
Input/Output (I/O)::How a program receives data (input) and produces results (output).
